  "informal_statement": "Let alpha, beta, gamma be preordered types. If f : alpha -> beta and g : beta -> gamma are both monotone, then their composition g . f : alpha -> gamma is monotone.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Unfold monotonicity directly: given a <= b, monotonicity of f gives f a <= f b, then monotonicity of g gives g (f a) <= g (f b), i.e. (g . f) a <= (g . f) b.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem monotone_comp {α β γ : Type*} [Preorder α] [Preorder β] [Preorder γ] (f : α → β) (g : β → γ) (hf : Monotone f) (hg : Monotone g) : Monotone (g ∘ f)",
